' -------------------------------------------------------------------------
' 1Ô∏è‚É£ Association ( -- or --> )
' -------------------------------------------------------------------------
' ‚Üí Basic link between classes (uses / has a connection)
' Syntax:   A -- B   or   A --> B
'
' Example:
'   Student --> Course : enrolls in >
'   Instructor --> Course : teaches >
'   Course --> Review : receives >
' Semantic meaning:
'   "A Student enrolls in a Course"
'   "An Instructor teaches a Course"
'   "A Course receives Reviews"
'
' -------------------------------------------------------------------------
' 2Ô∏è‚É£ Multiplicity
' -------------------------------------------------------------------------
' ‚Üí Defines how many instances relate
' Syntax:  "1", "0..1", "1..*", "*", "many"
'
' Example:
'   Course "1" -- "many" CourseContent : contains >
'   Student "1" -- "many" Enrollment : has >
' Meaning:
'   "One Course contains many CourseContents"
'   "One Student has many Enrollments"
'
' -------------------------------------------------------------------------
' 3Ô∏è‚É£ Aggregation ( o-- )
' -------------------------------------------------------------------------
' ‚Üí Weak ‚Äúhas-a‚Äù; parts can exist without the whole
' Symbol: hollow diamond (‚óá)
' Syntax:  Whole o-- Part
'
' Example:
'   Instructor o-- Course : teaches >
' Meaning:
'   "An Instructor teaches multiple Courses, but can exist without them"
'
' -------------------------------------------------------------------------
' 4Ô∏è‚É£ Composition ( *-- )
' -------------------------------------------------------------------------
' ‚Üí Strong ‚Äúowns-a‚Äù; part is destroyed with the whole
' Symbol: black diamond (‚óÜ)
' Syntax:  Whole *-- Part
'
' Example:
'   Course *-- CourseContent : contains >
'   Enrollment *-- Progress : tracks >
' Meaning:
'   "A Course owns its CourseContents ‚Äî if the course is deleted, contents are gone"
'   "An Enrollment tracks multiple Progress records ‚Äî delete enrollment, delete progress"
'
' -------------------------------------------------------------------------
' 5Ô∏è‚É£ Inheritance / Generalization ( <|-- )
' -------------------------------------------------------------------------
' ‚Üí ‚ÄúIs-a‚Äù relationship
' Syntax:  Child <|-- Parent
'
' Example:
'   Student <|-- User
'   Instructor <|-- User
' Meaning:
'   "A Student is a User"
'   "An Instructor is a User"
'
' -------------------------------------------------------------------------
' 6Ô∏è‚É£ Dependency ( ..> )
' -------------------------------------------------------------------------
' ‚Üí Temporary use (method, parameter, helper)
' Symbol: dashed arrow
'
' Example:
'   ReportService ..> User : uses >
' Meaning:
'   "ReportService uses User data temporarily to generate reports"
'
' -------------------------------------------------------------------------
' 7Ô∏è‚É£ Realization ( <|.. )
' -------------------------------------------------------------------------
' ‚Üí Class implements interface
' Syntax:  Class <|.. Interface
'
' Example:
'   PaymentService <|.. IPayment : implements >
' Meaning:
'   "PaymentService implements the IPayment interface"
'
' -------------------------------------------------------------------------
' üß≠ Direction & Semantics:
'   A --> B     ' A knows or acts on B
'   A <-- B     ' B knows or acts on A
'   A -- B      ' Both know each other
